
Overview of noun hardness

The noun hardness has 5 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                     
1. hardness -- (the property of being rigid and resistant to pressure; not easily scratched; measured on Mohs scale)
2. hardness -- (a quality of water that contains dissolved mineral salts that prevent soap from lathering; "the costs of reducing hardness depend on the relative amounts of calcium and magnesium compounds that are present")
3. unfeelingness, callousness, callosity, hardness, insensibility -- (devoid of passion or feeling; hardheartedness)
4. hardness, ruggedness -- (the quality of being difficult to do; "he assigned a series of problems of increasing hardness"; "the ruggedness of his exams caused half the class to fail")
5. severity, severeness, harshness, rigor, rigour, rigorousness, rigourousness, inclemency, hardness, stiffness -- (excessive sternness; "severity of character"; "the harshness of his punishment was inhuman"; "the rigors of boot camp")
